{"title":"First Look: KOM Cycling Unveils Quick Release Light 1000 and 350 Compact Headlights","link":"https://bikerumor.com/kom-cycling-quick-release-light-1000-and-350/","date":1743674287000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-front--1536x1152.webp\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" alt=\"KOM QR 100 and 350 front\" /></p>\n<p>KOM Cycling just dropped its latest innovation in bright bike lighting, and if you’re the kind of rider who swaps bikes like most people change socks — this one is for you. Meet the Quick Release Light 1000 and Quick Release Light 350 — two compact, high-powered solutions designed for easy-on, easy-off action without skimping performance.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>KOM Quick Release Light 1000 </strong>compact headlight</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle5.webp\"><img width=\"2048\" height=\"1178\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle5.webp\" alt=\"QRL02 Lifestyle5\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle5.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle5-297x171.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle5-1536x884.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle5-120x69.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle5-768x442.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The<a href=\"https://komcycling.com/products/quick-release-light-1000\" target=\"_blank\"> KOM 1000</a> throws out a hefty 1000 lumens (duh!), ensuring you’re not just seen, but practically lighting up the road ahead. Built to take on all conditions, it features multiple lighting modes, a solid rechargeable battery, and a waterproof design.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-details-.png\"><img width=\"1410\" height=\"1012\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-details-.png\" alt=\"KOM QR 350 details\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-details-.png 1410w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-details--297x213.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-details--120x86.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-details--768x551.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-weight--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-weight--1536x1152.webp\" alt=\"KOM QR 100 and 350 weight\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-weight--1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-weight--297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-weight--120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-weight--768x576.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-weight--2048x1536.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-1000-beams-and-350-.png\"><img width=\"1348\" height=\"994\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-1000-beams-and-350-.png\" alt=\"KOM QR 1000 beams and 350\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-1000-beams-and-350-.png 1348w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-1000-beams-and-350--297x219.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-1000-beams-and-350--120x88.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-1000-beams-and-350--768x566.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>The standout feature?</em></strong> A hinge-style adjustment system that lets you dial in the perfect beam angle. That 30° angle adjustment ensures you can see potholes and late-night creatures quickly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And, of course, the real magic is that KOM’s quick-release mount makes popping this light on and off your bars as effortless as flipping your bike computer on. This is where both KOM QR models really shine (<em>groan</em>). Both models work well with Garmin and Wahoo mounts, meaning less cockpit clutter and more streamlined setups. The lights mount on top of your standard GPS mount, then your GPS locks into place on top of the headlight. Or for out-front mounts with 1/4-turn interfaces top &amp; bottom, you can put the GPS on top and light down below.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Actual Weight:</strong>166g</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Price: </strong>$120</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>KOM Quick Release Light 350 is an even lighter, more compact headlight</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle2.webp\"><img width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle2.webp\" alt=\"QRL02 Lifestyle2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle2.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle2-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle2-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle2-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle2-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle2-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle2-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Do you need something smaller for daytime safety or city cruising? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>At less than half the weight, the <a href=\"https://komcycling.com/collections/cycling-lights/products/quick-release-light-350\" target=\"_blank\">Quick Release Light 350 </a>still packs 350 lumens into a sleek, lightweight unit with long runtimes. It gets the same quick-release treatment as its bigger sibling, so you won’t have to fiddle with annoying straps or rubber mounts. It just opts out of the up/down angle adjustability in the interest of simplicity. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-1000-inside-.png\"><img width=\"1410\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-1000-inside-.png\" alt=\"KOM QR 1000 inside\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-1000-inside-.png 1410w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-1000-inside--297x169.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-1000-inside--120x68.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-1000-inside--768x436.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-weight--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-weight--1536x1152.webp\" alt=\"KOM QR 350 weight\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-weight--1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-weight--297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-weight--120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-weight--768x576.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-weight--2048x1536.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-modes-.png\"><img width=\"1310\" height=\"1142\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-modes-.png\" alt=\"KOM QR 350 modes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-modes-.png 1310w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-modes--297x259.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-modes--120x105.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-350-modes--768x670.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Both models work well with Garmin (what we used) and Wahoo mounts, meaning less cockpit clutter and more streamlined setups. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Actual Weight:</strong> 75g</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> $60.00</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>First Impressions</strong> – QR 1000 Headlight Review</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-upclose--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-upclose--scaled.webp\" alt=\"KOM QR 100 and 350 upclose\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-upclose--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-upclose--297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-upclose--1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-upclose--120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-upclose--768x576.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-upclose--2048x1536.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The Quick Release Light 1000 </strong>is a solid choice for night rides, especially with that adjustable hinge — it’s a thoughtful touch many lights lack. The beam pattern is more of a<em> “to be seen” </em>rather than a wide <em>“to see.”</em> It would be a great addition to a headlamp if you do some late-day trail exploring on the commuter bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-30-deg--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-30-deg--scaled.webp\" alt=\"KOM QR 100 and 350 30 deg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-30-deg--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-30-deg--297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-30-deg--1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-30-deg--120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-30-deg--768x576.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-30-deg--2048x1536.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Easy Install </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s super easy to install, doesn’t add much (166g) to the front end, and looks tidy. I’ve yet to run out of charge on the QR 1000, but my pure nighttime riding is limited. I usually push the meter with dusk and<em> “make it home safe”</em> darkness. The KOM QR 1000 performed outstandingly in these conditions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We used the separate <a href=\"https://komcycling.com/products/cm06?variant=33275412611158\" target=\"_blank\">KOM CM06 QR mount</a> to hang both lights &amp; GPS devices in front of the bar for most riding, which costs $30 extra. It lets you put a Garmin or Wahoo computer on top and the KOM QR light underneath. It also comes with a GoPro adapter if you want to swap that light for an action cam sometimes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-front--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-front--scaled.webp\" alt=\"KOM QR 100 and 350 front\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-front--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-front--297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-front--1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-front--120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-front--768x576.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/KOM-QR-100-and-350-front--2048x1536.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The KOM QR1000 Light also functions as an excellent daytime running light and packs a seriously eye-catching zap in the daytime flash mode. Most of the time, I forget it was on my bars, and I soaked it on a rainy ride with zero issues or water ingress. My only gripe is the safety strap. It’s a non-stretchable lace material that holds the light if the carrier snaps. But I would rather see an elastic (like most headunit straps) tether that would be easier to attach and secure that light. The current tether doesn’t match the sleekness of the light design and seems a bit out of place.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>First Rides with the KOM QR 350 Headlight</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle6.webp\"><img width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle6.webp\" alt=\"QRL02 Lifestyle6\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle6.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle6-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle6-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle6-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle6-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle6-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/QRL02-Lifestyle6-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The KOM Quick Release 350</strong> is a great grab-and-go option for anyone who wants an extra layer of visibility without bulk. The quick-release system is the real star here, making these lights a no-brainer for multi-bike riders or anyone who hates fumbling with mounts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For the QR 350, I used it directly on my Garmin computer mount and then mounted my Garmin over it. The light added 10mm of stack to the Garmin mount, but I had peace of mind when on my road bike. It’s a simple and easy add-on that costs only $60 and offers nice visibility benefits.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://komcycling.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><em>KOMcycling.com</em></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/kom-cycling-quick-release-light-1000-and-350/\">First Look: KOM Cycling Unveils Quick Release Light 1000 and 350 Compact Headlights</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"415e311cc882724626f5def49338a25b573c3f24f364387dabba1d1f969daf43","category":"Cycling"}